Fresh-eyes review complete on `src/blog/people/drafts/Pete-Hegseth.md`. The notes are appended as a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-07-16)` comment block at the bottom of the file — no body edits made.

The two biggest issues:

1. **The 2019 war-crimes pardon lobbying is missing entirely.** Hegseth privately lobbied Trump for the Gallagher, Lorance, and Golsteyn pardons, and Trump cited him when they came through. It was the defining act of his Fox years and the direct precedent for the "kill them all" boat-strike section — right now the draft reads as if that reflex first appeared in 2025. Any reader who knows Hegseth will notice the hole.

2. **The flagship 32-day women-in-combat reversal is both overused and under-paid-off.** It's retold at full length in four places (TL;DR, two FAQs, diagnosis section, rabbit hole), with the 8-vs-3 pressure-test sentence appearing near-verbatim twice. And the draft resolves it too neatly as pure audience calibration, missing the 2026 payoff: he's reportedly been blocking female Navy admiral promotions without explanation — the podcast position quietly became policy while the Senate answer stays on tape. That's a darker, more type-precise close to the story.

Smaller notes in the block: the childhood section is the only one arguing from archetype instead of record (zero Forest Lake anecdotes), the deployments-and-faith tensions the working notes admit are quarantined in the rabbit hole instead of faced in the body, and the Trump audience-of-one dynamic is thin. On the plus side, the axe-throw open, the AAR bespoke form, and the extremist chapter's empathy turn are the strongest material and flagged for preservation.

Sources from the reality check: [TIME on Hegseth's pardon role](https://time.com/7176342/pete-hegseth-donald-trump-pardon-war-crimes-military/), [CNN on the private lobbying](https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/21/media/fox-news-pete-hegseth-trump-pardon-war-crimes), [Newsweek on the 2026 firings](https://www.newsweek.com/hegseth-pentagon-firings-generals-bipartisan-guardrails-12133372), [Daily Beast on blocked female promotions](https://www.thedailybeast.com/pentagon-pete-takes-aim-at-women-in-secret-crackdown/), [MS NOW on the religion-list cut](https://www.ms.now/opinion/pentagon-religion-list-pete-hegseth).
